
Predictive Stock Management System
UC-01: Login to System

Primary Actors: Admin, Store Manager, Inventory Staff

Preconditions

User is registered in the system

System is online

Main Flow

User enters username and password

System validates credentials

System grants access to the dashboard

Alternative Flows

AF1: Invalid credentials → system displays error message

AF2: Forgotten password → system redirects to password reset

Postconditions

User is successfully logged into the system

UC-02: Manage User Accounts

Primary Actor: Admin

Preconditions

Admin is logged in

Main Flow

Admin selects user management option

Admin adds/updates/deletes user accounts

System saves user details

Alternative Flows

AF1: Duplicate username → system shows warning

AF2: Invalid input → system requests correction

Postconditions

User account information is updated

UC-03: Record Sales Data

Primary Actors: Inventory Staff, Sales System

Preconditions

User/system is authenticated

Product exists in inventory

Main Flow

Sales data is entered or imported

System validates the data

Sales data is stored in database

Alternative Flows

AF1: Missing data → system prompts for completion

AF2: Invalid product ID → system rejects entry

Postconditions

Sales data is recorded successfully

UC-04: Update Inventory Levels

Primary Actor: Inventory Staff

Preconditions

User is logged in

Sales or delivery data is available

Main Flow

User selects inventory update option

System adjusts stock quantity

Updated inventory is saved

Alternative Flows

AF1: Negative stock detected → system blocks update

AF2: Product not found → system shows error

Postconditions

Inventory levels are updated

UC-05: View Stock Levels

Primary Actors: Store Manager, Inventory Staff

Preconditions

User is logged in

Main Flow

User requests stock status

System retrieves inventory data

System displays stock levels

Alternative Flows

AF1: No data available → system shows empty result

Postconditions

Current inventory status is displayed

UC-06: Predict Stock Demand

Primary Actors: Store Manager, Prediction Engine

Preconditions

Historical sales data exists

User is logged in

Main Flow

User initiates demand prediction

System analyzes sales data

Prediction engine generates forecast

System displays prediction results

Alternative Flows

AF1: Insufficient data → system shows warning

AF2: Prediction engine unavailable → system retries later

Postconditions

Stock demand prediction is generated

UC-07: Generate Restock Alerts

Primary Actor: System

Preconditions

Inventory thresholds are defined

Main Flow

System monitors stock levels

Stock falls below threshold

System generates alert notification

Alternative Flows

AF1: Threshold not set → alert not generated

Postconditions

Restock alert is sent to concerned users

UC-08: Place Restock Order

Primary Actor: Store Manager

Preconditions

User is logged in

Stock shortage identified

Main Flow

Manager reviews stock prediction

Manager selects supplier

Restock order is placed

System records order details

Alternative Flows

AF1: Supplier unavailable → select another supplier

AF2: Order cancelled → no changes made

Postconditions

Restock order is successfully placed

UC-09: Manage Supplier Details

Primary Actor: Admin

Preconditions

Admin is logged in

Main Flow

Admin opens supplier management

Admin adds/updates supplier details

System saves supplier information

Alternative Flows

AF1: Duplicate supplier entry → system shows error

Postconditions

Supplier details are updated

UC-10: Generate Reports

Primary Actors: Admin, Store Manager

Preconditions

User is logged in

Data is available

Main Flow

User selects report type

System collects required data

Report is generated and displayed

Alternative Flows

AF1: No data found → system shows message

AF2: User exports report → system saves file

Postconditions

Reports are generated and available for analysis

Result

All identified use cases were fully documented with preconditions, main flows, alternative flows, and postconditions.

Conclusion

Use case documentation provides a detailed understanding of system behavior and user interactions. The Predictive Stock Management System’s functionality was clearly defined through structured use case descriptions.
